## Dataset
- **Name:** Telco Customer Churn  
- **Source:** [Kaggle](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/blastchar/telco-customer-churn)  
- **Rows:** 7,043 customers  
- **Columns:** 21 features  
- **Target:** `Churn` — whether a customer left the company (Yes/No)

### Key Features
| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| `customerID` | Unique customer identifier (dropped during cleaning) |
| `gender` | Male or Female |
| `SeniorCitizen` | Whether customer is a senior citizen (0/1) |
| `tenure` | Number of months with the company |
| `PhoneService` | Whether customer has phone service |
| `InternetService` | DSL, Fiber optic, or None |
| `Contract` | Month-to-month, One year, Two year |
| `MonthlyCharges` | Monthly billing amount |
| `TotalCharges` | Total amount charged |
| `Churn` | **Target** — Yes if customer left, No if stayed |

### Business Problem
> A telecom company wants to identify **which customers are likely 
> to cancel their subscription** so the retention team can intervene 
> early with offers or support.
